# TypeScript Instructions

- Use explicit return types for exported functions and public methods.
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes and `type` for unions or mapped types.
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` with narrowing when needed.
- Keep React components small and focused; move business logic out of UI components.
- Follow naming and architecture rules in `AGENTS.md`.
